<pre>Hi!

This [[TiddlyWiki|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TiddlyWiki]] is a demo of ~TiddlyTemplating. The table below describes the examples. NB: You have to download this file and run locally to save files (see after the table for further info).

| ''Example'' | Tiddler to open | Description | Templates used |
|Creating RSS |[[templateTiddlers Test]] |Shows a RSS feed created using templates |RssTemplate, RssItemTemplate, RssItemCategoryTemplate |
|Saving RSS |n/a (see below) |The standard save for RSS has been overridden to work through the templates. (Caveat: because there is no [tag[!excludeLists]] filter syntax yet, this is using [tag[rss]] just to pop a couple of tiddlers into the output.) |//as above// |
|Previewing HTML file save |[[HtmlPageTemplate Test]] |Previews a mockup of a blog homepage using tiddlers tagged with "post". |HtmlPageTemplate, HtmlPagePostTemplate |
|Saving HTML files |[[HtmlSave Test]] |Creates a mockup of a blog homepage using tiddlers tagged with "post". (See the result at: http://tinyurl.com/23fqu7) |HtmlPageTemplate, HtmlPagePostTemplate |
|Saving CSV |[[CsvExample]] |Outputs a csv representation of tiddlers tagged with "rss". |CsvTemplate |

To [[download|http://jonny.jonathan.googlepages.com/TiddlyTemplating.html]] this page, ''right-click the link and hit "save as..."'' - run it locally and you can save files and edit the templates. To create a new template, create a new tiddler and tag it with "template".

Close and re-open a tiddler to re-run ListTemplate after making changes to a template it uses.

